abstract: Study published in journal Science Advances finds that immune systems of people with chronic fatigue syndrome differ from those of healthy people, and that recently diagnosed patients can be distinguished from those who have had the condition for longer.
lead_paragraph: Scientists have found biomarkers for chronic fatigue syndrome that may eventually form the basis of the first diagnostic test for it.

headline.main: Study on Chronic Fatigue May Help With Diagnoses
